article.headline: UC Davis 49, Brown 40
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. (AP) -- Vince Oliver scored 15 points, including a 3-pointer as time expired, to lift UC Davis to a 49-47 win over Brown. UC Davis (2-10) snapped a four-game losing streak with the victory in just its third home game of the season. Thomas Juillerat scored 13 points and added 12 rebounds for the Aggies. Chris Skrelja put in 12 points to lead Brown (5-9), who only shot 12-of-26 (46 percent) from the foul line. Mark McAndrew contributed 10 points to Brown's effort. UC Davis led 20-17 at halftime, but trailed 47-44 entering the final minute. Oliver hit a layup with 45.5 second remaining to cut the lead to one point. On the ensuing possession, UC Davis forced Brown into a shot clock violation. Aggie guard Rommel Marentez brought the ball up against pressure and found Oliver for an open shot from the elbow. UC Davis had been 2-for-18 from 3-point range until that point.
